The paper deals with decision problems related to graph partitioning and independent sets, which are typical topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The complexity analysis involves the use of computational complexity theory, which is a core topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The paper also considers parameters such as clique-width and neighborhood diversity, which are relevant to the study of graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of well-covered graphs is related to the study of graph theory and combinatorics (cs.GT). Finally, the paper deals with the recognition of graph properties, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
